data.text:
TULSA – A returning letterwinner … has played in 12 career games, all coming in 2023 … enrolled in January 2022 … became Tulsa’s second player in school history from Australia … a two-time academic all-conference honoree.

2023 – Played in all 12 games … had 19 stops and one pass breakup … saw his first career action in the season opener vs. UAPB and had one tackle … had a career-high four stops against both #19 OU and SMU … was named to the CSC Academic all-district team for football … was named one of the 2023 Military Bowl STEM Scholar-Athletes … earned academic all-conference honors.

2022 – Was one of several freshmen to sit out the season due to redshirt status … earned academic all-conference accolades.

HIGH SCHOOL – Was a two-year starter at Albany Creek State High School … played linebacker and defensive back on defense … on offense, played at running back, quarterback and slot … helped his team post a 10-2 record in 2019 and a 7-3 mark in 2020 … had 15 career TFL, six sacks and four interceptions and blocked one punt … also scored 26 touchdowns in his career … was his school’s 2020 Student of the Year … high school coach was Sam Harkness.

PERSONAL – Favorite NFL team is the New England Patriots … favorite NFL player is New York Jets linebacker Haason Reddick … his favorite book is Atomic Habits … lists his favorite vacation spots as the Daintree Rainforest and the Great Barrier Reef … favorite movie is Oppenheimer … his favorite sports movie is Invictus … co-founded an Australian NIL Agency … Connor McGregor is his favorite pro athlete … played the cello in primary school and double bass in early high school … began playing football at age 14 … has a younger sister … parents are Brian Neilsen and Janna Roop … majoring in mechanical engineering with a minor in economics … born in Grants, New Mexico.
